{"nodes":[{"content":"How Configuration Passes Work","pos":[34,63]},{"content":"How Configuration Passes Work","pos":[170,199]},{"content":"How Configuration Passes Work","pos":[207,236]},{"content":"Configuration passes are the phases of a Windows® installation during which you can customize an image.","pos":[239,342]},{"content":"Windows unattended installation settings can be applied in one or more configuration passes, depending on the setting you use.","pos":[343,469]},{"content":"Understanding how and when configuration passes run is very important in developing a Windows deployment strategy.","pos":[470,584]},{"content":"In this topic:","pos":[586,600]},{"content":"Understanding Configuration Passes","pos":[607,641]},{"content":"Configuring Device Drivers","pos":[662,688]},{"content":"Configuring International Settings","pos":[711,745]},{"content":"Examples","pos":[773,781]},{"pos":[856,890],"content":"Understanding Configuration Passes"},{"content":"The following diagram shows the relationship between the configuration passes relative to the different deployment tools.","pos":[893,1014]},{"content":"configuration passes overview","pos":[1018,1047]},{"content":"Not all configuration passes run in a particular installation of Windows.","pos":[1093,1166]},{"content":"Some configuration passes, such as <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>auditSystem<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>auditUser<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, run only if you boot the computer to audit mode.","pos":[1167,1285]},{"content":"Most Windows Setup unattend settings can be added to either the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>specialize<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> or the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>oobeSystem<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> configuration pass.","pos":[1286,1406]},{"content":"The other configuration passes can also be useful in certain situations.","pos":[1407,1479]},{"content":"The following table describes each of the configuration passes.","pos":[1480,1543]},{"content":"Configuration pass","pos":[1681,1699]},{"content":"Description","pos":[1722,1733]},{"content":"Configuration pass runs when","pos":[1756,1784]},{"content":"windowsPE","pos":[1858,1867]},{"content":"Many aspects of the installation process can be automated during the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>windowsPE<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> configuration pass.","pos":[1906,2021]},{"content":"In this pass you can configure:","pos":[2022,2053]},{"content":"Windows PE options","pos":[2070,2088]},{"content":"These options can include specifying the location of the Windows PE log file, which enables networking or a Windows PE page file.","pos":[2096,2225]},{"content":"Windows Setup options","pos":[2242,2263]},{"content":"These options can include specifying the Windows image to install and configuring a disk on the destination computer.","pos":[2271,2388]},{"content":"During this configuration pass, the Windows image is copied to the destination computer after the settings in the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>windowsPE<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> configuration pass are processed.","pos":[2407,2581]},{"content":"If your installation of Windows PE requires boot-critical drivers to access the local hard disk drive or a network, use this configuration pass to add drivers to the Windows PE driver store and to reflect the required boot-critical drivers","pos":[2589,2828]},{"content":"One of the following occurs:","pos":[2858,2886]},{"content":"Booting the Windows Setup media","pos":[2903,2934]},{"content":"Starting Windows Setup from a previous Windows installation","pos":[2951,3010]},{"content":"The Windows PE options are applied only when you are running Windows Setup from a Windows PE environment.","pos":[3029,3134]},{"content":"The Windows Setup options are applied when it runs from either Windows PE or a previous Windows installation.","pos":[3135,3244]},{"content":"offlineServicing","pos":[3306,3322]},{"content":"This configuration pass is used to apply updates, drivers, or language packs to a Windows image.","pos":[3361,3457]},{"content":"During Windows Setup, the Windows image is applied to a hard disk and any settings in the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>offlineServicing<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> section of an answer file are then applied to that image before the computer reboots.","pos":[3465,3674]},{"content":"During this configuration pass, you can add drivers to a Windows image before the image starts.","pos":[3682,3777]},{"content":"This enables you to install and process out-of-box device drivers during Windows Setup.","pos":[3778,3865]},{"content":"This configuration pass is also used to apply updates to a Windows image during servicing scenarios.","pos":[3873,3973]},{"content":"Automatically after the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>windowsPE<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> configuration pass and before the computer reboots.","pos":[4012,4114]},{"content":"During servicing scenarios when you specify an answer file by using the Deployment Image Servicing and Management tool (Dism.exe).","pos":[4131,4261]},{"content":"specialize","pos":[4333,4343]},{"content":"This configuration pass is used to create and configure information in the Windows image, and is specific to the hardware that the Windows image is installing to.","pos":[4382,4544]},{"content":"After the Windows image boots for the first time, the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>specialize<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> configuration pass runs.","pos":[4552,4658]},{"content":"During this pass, unique security IDs (SIDs) are created.","pos":[4659,4716]},{"content":"Additionally, you can configure many Windows features, including network settings, international settings, and domain information.","pos":[4717,4847]},{"content":"The answer file settings for the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>specialize<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> pass appear in audit mode.","pos":[4855,4942]},{"content":"When a computer boots to audit mode, the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>auditSystem<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> pass runs, and the computer processes the auditUser settings.","pos":[4943,5074]},{"content":"Automatically when the Windows image boots for the first time.","pos":[5113,5175]},{"content":"On the next boot after you run the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>sysprep<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> command with the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>/generalize<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> option.","pos":[5192,5305]},{"content":"generalize","pos":[5378,5388]},{"content":"During this configuration pass, computer-specific information is removed from the Windows installation enabling you to capture and reapply the Windows image to different computers.","pos":[5427,5607]},{"content":"For example, during this pass, the unique security ID (SID), unique device drivers, and other hardware-specific settings are removed from the image.","pos":[5608,5756]},{"content":"This configuration pass enables you to minimally configure the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>sysprep /generalize<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> command, in addition to configuring other Windows settings that must persist on your master image.","pos":[5764,5962]},{"content":"After the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>generalize<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> pass finishes, the next time that Windows image boots, the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>specialize<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> configuration pass runs.","pos":[5970,6119]},{"content":"If you want to retain the unique device drivers that are installed to your Windows installation, you can use the Microsoft-Windows-PnpSysprep | <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;code&gt;PersistAllDeviceInstalls&lt;/code&gt;</ph> setting.","pos":[6120,6310]},{"content":"If this setting is configured, unique device drivers are not removed from the installation.","pos":[6311,6402]},{"content":"The following setting is configured: Microsoft-Windows-Deployment | <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;code&gt;Generalize&lt;/code&gt;</ph>.","pos":[6441,6533]},{"content":"or -","pos":[6554,6558]},{"content":"Run the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>sysprep /generalize<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> command.","pos":[6575,6628]},{"content":"auditSystem","pos":[6700,6711]},{"content":"During this configuration pass, settings are processed when Windows is running in system context, before a user logs onto the computer in Aaudit mode.","pos":[6750,6900]},{"content":"This pass is typically used to make additional configurations to an installation, such as installing out-of-box device drivers.","pos":[6908,7035]},{"content":"This pass runs only when a computer is configured to boot to audit mode.","pos":[7043,7115]},{"content":"The following unattended Setup setting is configured: Microsoft-Windows-Deployment | Reseal | <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;code&gt; Mode&lt;/code&gt;=&lt;strong&gt;</ph>Audit<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph>.","pos":[7154,7290]},{"content":"or -","pos":[7311,7315]},{"content":"Run the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>sysprep<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> command with the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>/audit<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> option.","pos":[7332,7413]},{"content":"auditUser","pos":[7486,7495]},{"content":"This pass processes unattended Setup settings, after a user logs onto the computer in audit mode.","pos":[7534,7631]},{"content":"This pass is typically used to run custom commands or configure Windows Shell options.","pos":[7639,7725]},{"content":"This pass runs only when a computer is configured to boot to audit mode.","pos":[7733,7805]},{"content":"The following unattended Setup setting is configured: Microsoft-Windows-Deployment | Reseal | <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;code&gt; Mode&lt;/code&gt;=&lt;strong&gt;</ph>Audit<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph>.","pos":[7844,7980]},{"content":"or -","pos":[8001,8005]},{"content":"Run the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>sysprep<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> command with the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>/audit<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> option.","pos":[8022,8103]},{"content":"oobeSystem","pos":[8175,8185]},{"content":"During this configuration pass, settings are applied to Windows before Windows Welcome starts.","pos":[8224,8318]},{"content":"This pass is typically used to configure Windows Shell options, create user accounts, and specify language and locale settings.","pos":[8326,8453]},{"content":"The answer file settings for the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>oobeSystem<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> pass appear in Windows Welcome, also known as OOBE.","pos":[8461,8573]},{"content":"These settings do not appear in audit mode.","pos":[8574,8617]},{"content":"The following setting is configured: Microsoft-Windows-Deployment | <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;code&gt;Reseal&lt;/code&gt; | &lt;code&gt;Mode&lt;/code&gt;=&lt;strong&gt;</ph>OOBE","pos":[8656,8776]},{"content":"or -","pos":[8806,8810]},{"content":"Run the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>sysprep<ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> command with the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;strong&gt;</ph>/OOBE<ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;/strong&gt;</ph> option.","pos":[8827,8907]},{"content":"For more information about Windows components and settings that can be added to an answer file, see the Unattended Windows Setup Reference Guide.","pos":[8956,9101]},{"content":"For more information about logging, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Deployment Troubleshooting and Log Files<ept id=\"p1\">](deployment-troubleshooting-and-log-files.md)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Windows Setup Log Files and Event Logs<ept id=\"p2\">](windows-setup-log-files-and-event-logs.md)</ept>.","pos":[9102,9318]},{"pos":[9416,9442],"content":"Configuring Device Drivers"},{"content":"To add out-of-box, boot-critical drivers during an unattended installation, you must make sure that the boot-critical driver is available on preinstallation media.","pos":[9445,9608]},{"content":"Boot-critical drivers should be added during the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>windowsPE<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> configuration pass.","pos":[9609,9691]},{"content":"All drivers are staged in the driver store, but only boot-critical drivers are reflected or installed in the offline Windows image in addition to the Windows PE image.","pos":[9692,9859]},{"content":"Non-boot-critical drivers can be added to the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>offlineServicing<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> configuration pass.","pos":[9860,9946]},{"content":"This makes sure that boot-critical drivers are available and when the computer boots, the driver will load.","pos":[9947,10054]},{"pos":[10056,10166],"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Device Drivers and Deployment Overview<ept id=\"p1\">](device-drivers-and-deployment-overview.md)</ept>."},{"pos":[10279,10313],"content":"Configuring International Settings"},{"content":"International settings are available in multiple configuration passes, to enable you to customize the Windows image based on customer requirements and different deployment scenarios.","pos":[10316,10498]},{"content":"For example, if you build a computer in the United States (which would be an en-US international setting), you might perform all your tests in English.","pos":[10500,10651]},{"content":"However, if you intend to deliver the computer to France and need Windows to boot in French, you can add the fr-FR language pack, if the language pack is not already installed, and then configure the Microsoft-Windows-International-Core component to apply fr-FR settings during the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>specialize<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> configuration pass.","pos":[10652,10968]},{"content":"When the computer boots, the installation will display English text.","pos":[10969,11037]},{"content":"However, after the specialize configuration pass finishes, French text will be displayed.","pos":[11038,11127]},{"content":"You can use DISM to configure the language settings of a Windows image (either online or offline).","pos":[11129,11227]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt 