ings that you can configure during the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>windowsPE<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> configuration pass: Settings that apply to the Windows PE environment, such as the display resolution and log file locations for Windows PE.","pos":[12696,12926]},{"content":"You can also specify settings that apply to the Windows installation, such as configuring disk partitions or enabling dynamic updates.","pos":[12927,13061]},{"content":"The Windows PE-specific settings in an answer file are applied only when you are running Windows Setup from a Windows PE environment.","pos":[13071,13204]},{"pos":[13214,13363],"content":"The Windows Setup options in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>windowsPE<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> configuration pass are applied when it runs from either Windows PE or a previous Windows installation."},{"content":"After the Windows image is copied to the hard disk, the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>offlineServicing<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> configuration pass runs.","pos":[13369,13470]},{"content":"Any settings in the <ph id=\"ph1\">`&lt;servicing&gt;`</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">`&lt;settings pass=\"offlineServicing\"&gt;`</ph> section of an answer file are applied to the Windows image.","pos":[13471,13605]},{"content":"Typically, the actions in this configuration pass install or remove packages, language packs, or device drivers.","pos":[13606,13718]},{"content":"The system restarts and Windows Setup runs the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>specialize<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> configuration pass.","pos":[13724,13805]},{"content":"At this point, settings in the <ph id=\"ph1\">`&lt;settings pass=\"specialize\"&gt;`</ph> section of the answer file are processed.","pos":[13806,13909]},{"content":"After Windows Setup completes, the computer restarts.","pos":[13915,13968]},{"content":"Then, the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>oobeSystem<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> configuration pass runs and settings in the <ph id=\"ph1\">`&lt;settings pass=\"oobeSystem&gt;`</ph> section of an answer file are processed.","pos":[13969,14108]},{"pos":[14114,14708],"content":"**Note**  \nYou can create a separate content file called Oobe.xml that you can use to customize Windows Welcome, Getting Started, and ISP sign up. Using Oobe.xml is useful for organizing these customizations, because it enables you to maintain a single file that lists all of the branding, license terms, and signup opportunities for multiple countries, regions and/or languages. For more information, see [Configure Oobe.xml](configure-oobexml.md). Generally, Oobe.xml is used by OEMs and System Builders. However some aspects of Oobe.xml might also benefit corporate deployment scenarios.","leadings":["","    "],"nodes":[{"content":"Note","pos":[2,6]},{"content":"You can create a separate content file called Oobe.xml that you can use to customize Windows Welcome, Getting Started, and ISP sign up. Using Oobe.xml is useful for organizing these customizations, because it enables you to maintain a single file that lists all of the branding, license terms, and signup opportunities for multiple countries, regions and/or languages. For more information, see [Configure Oobe.xml](configure-oobexml.md). Generally, Oobe.xml is used by OEMs and System Builders. However some aspects of Oobe.xml might also benefit corporate deployment scenarios.","pos":[11,590],"nodes":[{"content":"You can create a separate content file called Oobe.xml that you can use to customize Windows Welcome, Getting Started, and ISP sign up.","pos":[0,135]},{"content":"Using Oobe.xml is useful for organizing these customizations, because it enables you to maintain a single file that lists all of the branding, license terms, and signup opportunities for multiple countries, regions and/or languages.","pos":[136,368]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Configure Oobe.xml<ept id=\"p1\">](configure-oobexml.md)</ept>.","pos":[369,438]},{"content":"Generally, Oobe.xml is used by OEMs and System Builders.","pos":[439,495]},{"content":"How